The paper discusses a benchmark suite for sparse tensor algorithms, which are commonly used in machine learning, quantum chemistry, healthcare analytics, social network analysis, data mining, and signal processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Other possible sub-categories include cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
